@startuml
[*] --> NormalState

state "Normal State" as NormalState
NormalState : entry / Initial state
NormalState : do / Display current time
NormalState : exit / Button pressed to adjust time

NormalState --> AdjustingTime : button pressed (adjust time)

state "Adjusting Time" as AdjustingTime
AdjustingTime : entry / Adjusting time/settings
AdjustingTime : do / Change hour, minutes, alarm hour, or alarm minutes
AdjustingTime : exit / Button released or next adjustment

AdjustingTime --> IncreasingValue : increase value
IncreasingValue : entry / Increase value
IncreasingValue : do / Increase value
IncreasingValue : exit / Decrease value button pressed or time adjustment button pressed again
IncreasingValue --> AdjustingTime : decrease value button pressed
IncreasingValue --> NormalState : time adjustment button pressed

AdjustingTime --> AlarmState : alarm time reached

state "Alarm State" as AlarmState
AlarmState : entry / Alarm triggered
AlarmState : do / Ring alarm
AlarmState : exit / Button pressed to stop alarm

AlarmState --> AlarmOff : button pressed (stop alarm)

state "Alarm Off" as AlarmOff
AlarmOff : entry / Alarm stopped
AlarmOff : do / No alarm active
AlarmOff : exit / Return to normal state

AlarmOff --> NormalState : button released

NormalState --> LightOn : button pressed (light on)

state "Light On" as LightOn
LightOn : entry / Light activated
LightOn : do / Light is on
LightOn : exit / Button released

LightOn --> NormalState : button released

Idle --> AlarmOff : current time matches alarm time
AlarmOff --> Idle : stop alarm button pressed
@enduml
